<br>
Few quick things to note...<br>
<br>
If your really dating the changes over time, do not count harvest in &quot;old world&quot; although it is available at level 34, it sure was not there back in the day. It was added late kunark was it not? Cannot remember specificly.<br>
<br>
Wrt epic, add that 3 mana per tic into kunark numbers as well.<br>
<br>
I am in no way knocking your numbers, or the time it took you to do this, it was a very valid attempt to get real representation and comparison for the classes. There are some assumptions made on your behalf though upon spell selection of the wizard class, I cannot speak for other classes but you may of made some there as well. It was a very good move to post a thread on the other class boards to try and get feedback to then alter the numbers a bit. <br>
<br>
For example, just alternating ice spear + nuke robe, a wizard can sustain over 100dps for extended periods of time. This combination was available as early as velious (ice spear was from SoV, rend robe from kunark and verm robe from SoV, numbers will vary dependant on the robe though). <br>
<br>
And for the people giving him a hard time with regards to aggro and chain nuking, with EB weapons on our warriors (and he is using some endgame analysis wrt rare/ancient nukes) I can and have pushed 150+ dps on fights without getting summoned, till the MT died at least =0 )~ So to assume that chain nuking can or will not happen in the real world is a bit off. You may have to mix up what nukes you actually use, but most good casters I know, chain nuke all the time. <br>
<br>
Which brings me to another drawback of this comparison with nukes, it does not quite reflect reality. Reality has you mixxing certain nukes (you did try to cover this with ADoI/IS), rains, items. The realistic situation created by this &quot;mixxing&quot; is a bit off from the numbers your trying to compare. Which is why someone raised the question of Enchanters possibly outnuking a wizard, which in reality... just ain't gonna happen. <p><br><br><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22676" target=blank><IMG SRC="http://www.eqcompanions.com/files/mandosig4.jpg" border="0"></a>
